description:
&lt;p&gt;The Combined Adult and Enhanced Care Pathway of the Bury South Integrated Delivery Team has an exciting opportunity for a Senior Community Mental Health Nurse (Band 6) to join our multi-disciplinary team supporting service users in their recovery from severe mental illness. Our teams cover the towns in Suffolk of Bury Saint Edmunds, Haverhill, and Sudbury. Right now is a fantastic time for a career in adult community mental health services, as you will join us at the very forefront of designing the pioneering services of the future in community care. Experience of working to aspirational Recovery Model principles within the Care Program Approach would be desirable but inhouse training will be provided if not.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer the opportunity to work with a supportive and friendly team in an environment where the successful candidate will receive regular management and clinical supervision. We are also keen to invest in staff development as we are committed to continual appraisal of your training needs. There are many areas of career development that we can offer you. The operating hours of our service is Monday – Friday 09:00-17:00.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits included with this role are:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A comprehensive in house &amp; external training program’s&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Career progression&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Starting annual leave of 27 days per annum increasing to 33 days pa based on length of service (plus paid bank holidays)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staff physio service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts and many more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here at NSFT we pride ourselves on being a welcoming, talented, friendly and supportive team who like nothing better than sharing their experiences and learning from each other.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This multi-disciplinary team includes a Consultant Psychiatrist, Psychiatric Nurses, Non-Medical Nurse Prescribers, Mental Health Social Workers, Psychologists, Locality Lead Assessors, Community Health Connectors, a Physical Health Team, and Support Workers &amp; Peer Support Workers as well as Carer Leads and ADHD specialists. We work as an integrated health and social care team with great links to the community to promote individual’s independence as they move towards their recovery and discharge from secondary services. We look forward to having you join us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please find attached our Job Description and Person Specification for more detail on your Key Accountabilities, then if you feel you have what it takes to make a difference in your local communities, click APPLY!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Interviews are to be confirmed, candidates may only be given a minimum of 3 days’ notice, please note this date is provisional and may be subject to change. You will be contacted via email and invited to book a time. These emails may go to your SPAM, so please keep checking all your emails if applying.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please visit our Facebook and Twitter page @NSFTjobs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Peter Henson Job title Community Teams Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address peter.henson@nsft.nhs.uk Telephone number 01284 733188&lt;/p&gt;
